  "prompt": "Can we know if our card has been inserted in ATM?",
  "response": "Yes, most ATMs provide some sort of indication when a card has been successfully inserted and recognized. Typically, here's what you can expect:\n\n1. **Visual Confirmation**: Many ATMs have lights or screens that will display messages indicating that the card has been inserted correctly.\n\n2. **Screen Prompts**: Once the card is inserted, the ATM's screen will usually prompt you to enter your PIN or choose a transaction type, confirming that it has detected the card.\n\n3. **Audible Feedback**: Some ATMs may provide sounds or beeps as an indication that the card is recognized.\n\nIf you do not see any indication after inserting your card, it could be due to a malfunction or an issue with the card itself. In such cases, it's advisable to check your card for any damage or try using a different ATM.",
